HTML: Estructura d'una pàgina.
CSS: Maquetar el CSS i donar-li un layout.
JS: Donar-li interacció. Control behavior of different elements.
JS: Object-oriented. No distinction between types of objects.
Java: Class-based.
DOM: Document Object Mode (https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document_Object_Model) API que permet manipular l'HTML. Crea un àrbre de nodes que pot modificar el document.
ECMAScript5: "use strict" per a utilizar versions modernes.
Page events: DOMContentLoaded (The browser fully loaded HTML. When the DOM is ready, so the handler can lookup DOM nodes, initialize the interface. Not okey for images.) Use: document.addListenr('DOMContentLoaded', main);
Creating elements: document.createElement(tag)
                   document.createElement(div)
Insertion methods: node.append(...nodes or strings)/afig sempre al final

Method querySelector: document.querySelector(element)/only one.  document.querySelectorAll(element)/all elements.
Event handling: Code structures that listen for activity in the browser, and run code in response.

JSON: Transmetre, emmagatzemar i transmetre comunicacions. Igual que HTML, pero basat en java.

Built-in Object: Math, Array
Array: mix of different date types. Accessed using integers as indexes. Index 0. 
